## Proposed Changes

### 1. Clerk Authentication
- **Frontend:** Install `@clerk/clerk-react`, wrap app in `<ClerkProvider>`, and use `<SignIn />` / `<SignUp />`.
- **Backend:** Replace `/login` and `/register` with Clerk JWT verification in `auth.py`. Auto-sync Clerk users to Supabase.

### 2. Supabase & Upstash Databases
- **SQL & Vectors:** Connect SQLAlchemy to Supabase. Update `models.py` to use `pgvector` for agent memories instead of Qdrant.
- **Redis:** Update `celery_app.py` to securely connect to Upstash using `rediss://`.

### 3. Razorpay Payments
#### [MODIFY] backend/payments.py
- Remove the `stripe` package and import `razorpay`.
- Create `/create-order` endpoint to generate Razorpay orders instead of Stripe Checkout sessions.
- Replace Stripe Webhook logic with Razorpay Webhook signature verification (`razorpay_signature`).

#### [MODIFY] backend/models.py
- Rename `stripe_customer_id` and `stripe_charge_id` to `razorpay_customer_id`, `razorpay_order_id`, and `razorpay_payment_id` in `User` and `Transaction` models.

#### [MODIFY] src/components/Checkout.tsx (Frontend)
- Integrate Razorpay Checkout UI instead of Stripe redirect logic.

### 4. Composio Integrations
#### [MODIFY] backend/models.py
- Update the `Integration` model. Instead of storing manual `access_token`s, we will store a `composio_entity_id`.

#### [MODIFY] backend/agents/agent_handler.py & Node Graphs
- Install `composio-core` and its specific agent plugins (e.g. `composio-langchain` or `composio-openai`).
- Bind Composio tools to the agents natively, so they can autonomously interact with platforms (like Meta, Twitter, LinkedIn) via the Composio platform without manual API routing.

